  <h3>What is a Decentralized Exchange (DEX)?</h3>
    <p>A Decentralized Exchange, or DEX, is a special type of cryptocurrency exchange that doesn't rely on a central authority to handle transactions. Instead, it allows users to trade directly with each other.</p>
    <p>Think of it like a digital marketplace where you can swap your cryptocurrencies with others who are looking to trade. The exchange happens through smart contracts, which are like automatic agreements that make sure everything goes smoothly.</p>
    <p>DEXs give you more control over your trades and provide benefits like increased privacy and reduced risk of someone else mishandling your funds. Plus, they fit in perfectly with the idea of decentralization, where no single authority has all the power.</p>


